{{Expand|date=November 2008}}
[[George W. Bush]]'s political positions have been expressed in public statements, and through his actions as [[President of the United States]].
==Economic policy==
===Fiscal policy and taxation===
===Energy policy===

George Bush supports [[nuclear power|nukuler power]] and opposes [[green energy]]. He unsigned the [[Kyoto Protocol]] and supports drilling in [[ANWR]].
===Free-market capitalism===

Bush is a supporter of [[free trade]], calling on nations to embrace free trade even as turmoil raced through the world's markets in the [[2008 financial crisis]]. <ref>http://www.boston.com/news/world/asia/articles/2008/11/23/bush_promotes_free_trade_at_asia_pacific_summit_in_peru/</ref>

===Trade===
===Subprime mortgage crisis relief===
===Health care===

In [[2004]], Bush planned a health care program that would supposedly cover as many as 10 million people who lack health insurance at a cost of $102 billion over the next decade, though the [[Washington Post]] is skeptical. <ref>http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/articles/A21929-2004Aug21.html</ref>

