==Social policy==
===Abortion===

Bush has a strong [[anti-abortion]] stance, voting consistently [[pro-life]] and supports [[parental notification]] for minor girls who want abortions. <ref>http://www.ontheissues.org/george_w__bush.htm</ref>

===From Childhood to retirement===
===Crime===

Bush is a big fan of the [[death penalty]], and carried out over 150 executions as governor of [[Texas]]. <ref>http://www.texecutions.com/</ref>

===Education===
===Electoral College===
===Environment===

Bush has an anti-environmental voting record. In 2000, he said "Weaken Clean Air; no comment on Clean Water." <ref>http://www.ontheissues.org/george_w__bush.htm</ref> Bush<U+2019>s environmental record in Texas is notably poor, and he has never suggested he cares. On his watch, the air in Houston has become so foul that the city has recently displaced Los Angeles as the city with the worst smog in America. <ref>http://www.ontheissues.org/Celeb/George_W__Bush_Environment.htm</ref>

===LGBT issues===
Bush opposes [[same-sex marriage]]. During his [[George W. Bush presidential campaign, 2004|2004 reelection campaign]], he called for an [[List of amendments to the United States Constitution|amendment to the U.S. Constitution]] that would [[Federal Marriage Amendment|ban same-sex marriage]] in the United States.

===Islam===
===Prayer in public schools===
===Stem cell research===
Bush opposes federal funding for [[embryonic stem cell|embryonic]] forms of [[stem cell]] research.

===Medical marijuana and marijuana decriminalization===

Bush opposes medical marijuana and marijuana decriminalization.

===Video game regulation===
===Internet Neutrality===

Bush opposses Network Neutrality.

